&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teads is a leading omnichannel advertising platform focused on driving outcomes for brand and performance advertisers across screens. With a focus on meaningful business outcomes for branding and performance objectives, Teads drives value by leveraging predictive AI technology to connect quality media, beautiful brand creative, and context-driven addressability and measurement. Teads is directly partnered with more than 10,000 publishers and 20,000 advertisers globally. The company is headquartered in New York, New York with a global team of around 1,700 people in 30+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.teads.com&quot;&gt;www.teads.com.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position, you will be a key contributor to our financial operations. You will ensure high-quality financial data management using &lt;strong&gt;NetSuite&lt;/strong&gt; and provide critical support to the Head of Finance CEE. This is an ideal role for an accountant with 3–5 years of experience who thrives in a tech-forward, international environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and update the general ledger, ensuring all entries are accurate and compliant with local standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Accounts Payable (AP) and Accounts Receivable (AR) processes within &lt;strong&gt;NetSuite&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the monthly, quarterly and year-end closing procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform detailed bank reconciliations and monitor daily cash flow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare mandatory tax filings (VAT, VIES, SAF-T etc.) and ensure compliance with Romanian fiscal regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Head of Finance CEE with ad-hoc financial analysis and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously optimize NetSuite workflows to increase departmental efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you bring to the team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 3–5 years of solid accounting experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Software:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven proficiency in &lt;strong&gt;NetSuite ERP&lt;/strong&gt; (mandatory) and &lt;strong&gt;Advanced Excel&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Degree in Finance, Accounting, or a similar field. CECCAR certification is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Languages:&lt;/strong&gt; Fluency in &lt;strong&gt;English&lt;/strong&gt; is essential for daily collaboration with international stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Soft Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Analytical mindset, proactivity, and the ability to work effectively in a hybrid, fast-paced setup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please submit your CV in English.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Life at Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Teads, we don’t just offer new roles - we blend creativity, technology, and data to shape the future of media. You’ll work with smart humans, meaningful brands, and cool tools, all while helping redefine how advertising works in a world that demands more transparency, better insights, and smarter strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Teadster, you’ll play a critical role in shaping our future success in the region. Here’s why Teads stands out:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We&#39;ve merged two open internet category leaders—Outbrain and Teads—to create the ‘new’ Teads, a unified omnichannel platform that drives results from branding to performance across all screens, including CTV, mobile, and web.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As part of our

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teads is a leading omnichannel advertising platform focused on driving outcomes for brand and performance advertisers across screens. With a focus on meaningful business outcomes for branding and performance objectives, Teads drives value by leveraging predictive AI technology to connect quality media, beautiful brand creative, and context-driven addressability and measurement. Teads is directly partnered with more than 10,000 publishers and 20,000 advertisers globally. The company is headquartered in New York, New York with a global team of around 1,700 people in 30+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.teads.com&quot;&gt;www.teads.com.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an &lt;strong&gt;Account Manager Assistant,&lt;/strong&gt; you will be part of the Account Management team and help manage advertising campaigns validated by the sales team and maintain daily relationships with agencies and advertisers. &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a 1 year apprentice.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The interviews will be conducted in French.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in implementation, across all stages, of setting up advertising campaigns online&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help in analysis, optimization and recommendations of areas for improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in performance reports and post-campaign analysis (weekly or monthly)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get involved in daily monitoring of campaigns to ensure a 100% delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationship with the sales team in pre-sales support and in the daily management of the region/country, and optimizations on the broadcast network with publishers teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you bring to the team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are passionate about the world of online advertising, new media and you want to have a first experience in video and new advertising formats on the web&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently studying the last year of Business Administration, Marketing, Economics, Advertising or similar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are rigorous, organized and autonomous&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You demonstrate a good sense of analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have some business sense and good relationship skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You control the basic functionality of Microsoft Office&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;French and English is mandatory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-have&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Some knowledge of the different tracking tools, the operation of an ad server, different actors and processes SSP, RTB, ADEX is a plus&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please submit your CV in English.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Life at Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Teads, we don’t just offer new roles - we blend creativity, technology, and data to shape the future of media. You’ll work with smart humans, meaningful brands, and cool tools, all while helping redefine how advertising works in a world that demands more transparency, better insights, and smarter strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Teadster, you’ll play a critical role in shaping our future success in the region. Here’s why Teads stands out:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We&#39;ve merged two open internet category leaders—Outbrain and Teads—to create the ‘new’ Teads, a unified omnichannel platform that drives results from branding to performance across all screens, includi

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teads is a leading omnichannel advertising platform focused on driving outcomes for brand and performance advertisers across screens. With a focus on meaningful business outcomes for branding and performance objectives, Teads drives value by leveraging predictive AI technology to connect quality media, beautiful brand creative, and context-driven addressability and measurement. Teads is directly partnered with more than 10,000 publishers and 20,000 advertisers globally. The company is headquartered in New York, New York with a global team of around 1,700 people in 30+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.teads.com&quot;&gt;www.teads.com.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the role of an Accounts Receivable &amp;amp; Collections Analyst, you will be instrumental to our financial operations by managing and optimizing the accounts receivable process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position involves overseeing collections across a global portfolio to maintain its credit quality. You will also be responsible for delivering timely internal reporting and analysis on debtor balances, cash collections, and bad debts, while sustaining professional communication with customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A day in the life&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact customers (agencies, publishers and brand clients) by telephone, email and letter to encourage collection in assigned portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain positive relationship with our customers by providing excellent service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain notes on follow up and contact within NetSuite (our ERP system) and Salesforce (CRM)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle cases and Financial Requests relating to customers’ AR position via Salesforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Send monthly statements to customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reduce DSO and bad debt expense of assigned portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication to Sales and Account Managers on status of their accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support daily cash applications in NetSuite and investigate unallocated cash receipts to customer accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issue reminder and legal notices to customers based on the Credit Control policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Internal Sales, AMs, Finance, Legal and billing teams in order to resolve discrepancies in a timely manner&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and report on potential bad debts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Determine when accounts should be sent to outside collection agency when all efforts have been exhausted&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly reporting metrics on performance of portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assist in setting credit limits for new and existing customers where needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with customer credit card matters such as cc charges, refunds, chargebacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other ad-hoc projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 6 years experience in an Accounts Receivable / Collections role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to adjust priorities quickly under pressure to meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility within a constantly changing environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to cooperate and collaborate effectively with team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven results in reducing debtor days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive attitude – ability to take initiative to get things done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess strong Microsoft Excel and IT skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be motiva

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teads is a leading omnichannel advertising platform focused on driving outcomes for brand and performance advertisers across screens. With a focus on meaningful business outcomes for branding and performance objectives, Teads drives value by leveraging predictive AI technology to connect quality media, beautiful brand creative, and context-driven addressability and measurement. Teads is directly partnered with more than 10,000 publishers and 20,000 advertisers globally. The company is headquartered in New York, New York with a global team of around 1,700 people in 30+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.teads.com&quot;&gt;www.teads.com.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a &lt;strong&gt;Fixed-Term Contract – Maternity Leave Replacement,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;and it sits within our Native Performance team, reporting directly to the Director of Product, Amplify. The Native Performance team sits at the heart of Teads&#39; advertiser offering. Our mission is to enable performance-focused advertisers to reach their audiences through high-quality native formats (including in-feed, in-article, and banner placements) on the open internet. We drive measurable outcomes by combining native formats with smart automation, AI-powered optimization, and campaign tooling through the Amplify platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Mission&lt;/strong&gt;: Join us on a fixed-term basis (covering a maternity leave) to drive the development, optimization, and scaling of Amplify&#39;s native performance capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Alignment:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner hand-in-hand with agile engineering squads, product designers, data scientists, and business stakeholders to turn ambitious ideas into seamless platform features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scope of Ownership&lt;/strong&gt;: Take full ownership of the Native Performance feature roadmap—guiding features from initial discovery and scoping to shipping and post-launch optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact Metric&lt;/strong&gt;: Success in this role means maintaining pipeline velocity, shipping key AI and automation initiatives on schedule, and ensuring a seamless transition and continuous feature adoption across global commercial teams during the coverage period.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Strategy &amp;amp; Innovation&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orchestrate AI &amp;amp; Automation Features: Lead the development of smart, automated capabilities within Amplify, such as automated campaign creation, dynamic setup recommendations, and predictive performance alerts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze Market Trends: Conduct competitive analysis and track industry shifts within native and performance advertising to champion new feature opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Challenge the Status-Quo: Adopt our collaborative product mantra (&lt;em&gt;&quot;You build it, you run it, you monitor it&quot;&lt;/em&gt;), bringing a pragmatic, solution-driven mindset to propose bold platform improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Execution &amp;amp; Flawless Delivery&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the Amplify Roadmap: Manage and prioritize the feature backlog, tracking milestones, dependencies, and delivery risks for the Native Performance agile squad.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate Needs into Specs: Write clear, concise product requirements, user stories, and functional specifications for our development teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Agile Ceremonies: Direct sprint planning, review sessions, and blameless retrospectives, serving as a senior product voi

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teads is a leading omnichannel advertising platform focused on driving outcomes for brand and performance advertisers across screens. With a focus on meaningful business outcomes for branding and performance objectives, Teads drives value by leveraging predictive AI technology to connect quality media, beautiful brand creative, and context-driven addressability and measurement. Teads is directly partnered with more than 10,000 publishers and 20,000 advertisers globally. The company is headquartered in New York, New York with a global team of around 1,700 people in 30+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.teads.com&quot;&gt;www.teads.com.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the opportunity&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Cloud Engineer to join a team of talented engineers who build premium solutions at scale. Every day, we tackle ambiguous and stimulating challenges.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join a highly experienced team who builds quality and responsible advertising, at scale!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our main Engineering challenges at Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Working in a very high-traffic environment (2.2 billion users per month, 100 billion events per day) with low latency and high availability constraints (2 million requests per second, responses in less than 150 milliseconds).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Rich and diverse tech stack and system architecture to optimize for performance, scalability, resiliency, and cost efficiency. We use mostly Java, Scala, Golang, Python, and TypeScript, among others.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Management of large datasets with milliseconds order of magnitude access time, to compute in a near real-time complex auction resolution algorithm (18 million predictions per second).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Build efficient and easy-to-use web products used by thousands of users working for the world&#39;s most premium publishers, advertisers, and agencies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;A fast-changing environment where we continuously collaborate with Product teams and constantly adapt our Cloud infrastructure for new features and Products.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Bring a wide diversity of profiles to the same level of quality and knowledge.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Our Infrastructure Team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Running on public cloud providers (AWS, Azure, GCP) as well as on-premise data centers, we are a growing team intentionally composed of diverse skills sets (development obviously, but also data store, software reliability, operational automation, etc.) which aims at delivering a first-class platform for our product development teams. We embrace&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Reliability Engineering&lt;/strong&gt;, toil is our enemy while automation at scale is our main ally.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong data-stringify-type=&quot;bold&quot;&gt;About Teads&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Teads is a leading omnichannel advertising platform focused on driving outcomes for brand and performance advertisers across screens. With a focus on meaningful business outcomes for branding and performance objectives, Teads drives value by leveraging predictive AI technology to connect quality media, beautiful brand creative, and context-driven addressability and measurement. Teads is directly partnered with more than 10,000 publishers and 20,000 advertisers globally. The company is headquartered in New York, New York with a global team of around 1,700 people in 30+ countries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information, visit &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.teads.com&quot;&gt;www.teads.com.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ポジションの概要&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Teads Japanの&lt;strong&gt;コマーシャル・ディレクター&lt;/strong&gt;として、クライアントにとって信頼できるアドバイザー、チームのメンター、そして組織全体の重要なコラボレーターとしての役割を担っていただきます。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;カントリーマネージャーに直属し、トップクラスの広告主や代理店におけるTeadsプレゼンスの拡大、戦略的成長、長期的なパートナーシップ、そして大胆な発想を推進する責任者です。鋭いビジネス嗅覚と起業家精神を持ち、TVなどの従来のメディアからデジタル領域までシームレスに活躍できる方を求めています。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;主な職務内容&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;事業拡大の推進:&lt;/strong&gt; 主要な広告代理店およびブランドとの関係を強化し、エグゼクティブレベルとの信頼関係を構築する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;セールスサイクルの統括:&lt;/strong&gt; リードの特定からピッチ、クロージングまでを一貫して行い、実利的なビジネス成果を創出する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ソリューションの提言:&lt;/strong&gt; クライアントの課題に対し、Teadsが誇る市場をリードするフォーマットや知見を活用した最適な広告ソリューションを提案する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;戦略的パートナーシップ:&lt;/strong&gt; 戦略的パートナーとして、アカウントの成長とイノベーションの機会を継続的に模索する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;リーダーシップの発揮:&lt;/strong&gt; セールス、アカウントマネジメント、キャンペーンマネジメントの各チームに対し、明確な戦略提示、パフォーマンス分析、メンターシップを通じて指導・育成を行う。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;社内連携:&lt;/strong&gt; 社内各部署（キャンペーンマネジメント、スタジオ、データ＆インサイト、サプライ）と協力し、高品質なキャンペーンを構築する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;提案活動:&lt;/strong&gt; クライアントに響くカスタマイズされたピッチ資料やRFP（提案依頼書）への回答を作成する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;契約交渉:&lt;/strong&gt; クライアントの目標を深く理解し、商業的な視点を持って契約交渉をリードする。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;収益管理:&lt;/strong&gt; 規律あるパイプライン管理と正確な予測により、健全かつ予測可能な収益を確保する。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;市場トレンドの把握:&lt;/strong&gt; 常に市場動向を先取りし、その知見をチームやクライアントへのアクションへと昇華させる。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;応募資格&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;経験:&lt;/strong&gt; 10年以上のセールス経験。そのうち5年以上はリーダーシップポジションにおいて、代理店やブランドの成功を牽引した実績があること。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;業界知識:&lt;/strong&gt; 国内広告代理店との業務経験、および新規事業開発のバックグラウンドは必須。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;デジタル知見:&lt;/strong&gt; デジタル広告業界およびプログラマティック広告に関する深い理解は必須。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;テクニカルスキル:&lt;/strong&gt; アドサーバー、トラッキング技術、効果測定ソリューションに関する十分な知識。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ネットワーク:&lt;/strong&gt; 日本の広告エコシステム（クリエイティブ・メディア担当代理店、トレーディングデスク、主要ブランドのステークホルダーなど）における強固な人脈。&lt;/li&gt;
